{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":914,"text":"I'm a relationship builder."},{"time":3144,"text":"When you think of a relationship builder,"},{"time":5140,"text":"don't you just automatically\nthink \"architect?\""},{"time":7922,"text":"Probably not."},{"time":10077,"text":"That's because most people think\narchitects design buildings and cities,"},{"time":14307,"text":"but what we really design\nare relationships,"},{"time":17383,"text":"because cities are about people."},{"time":19514,"text":"They're places where people come together\nfor all kinds of exchange."},{"time":22920,"text":"And besides, skylines\nare highly specific urban habitats"},{"time":26161,"text":"with their own insects,\nplants and animals,"},{"time":28503,"text":"and even their own weather."}]},{"cues":[{"time":30650,"text":"But today, urban habitats\nare out of balance."},{"time":33803,"text":"Climate change, together with political\nand economic troubles,"},{"time":37859,"text":"are having an impact;"},{"time":39035,"text":"they're adding up\nand stressing out cities and us,"},{"time":42371,"text":"the people who live in them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":45000,"text":"For me, the field of ecology\nhas provided important insight,"},{"time":48649,"text":"because ecologists don't just look\nat individual species on their own,"},{"time":52882,"text":"they look at the relationships\nbetween living things"},{"time":56099,"text":"and their environment."},{"time":58554,"text":"They look at how all the diverse parts\nof the ecosystem are interconnected,"},{"time":62456,"text":"and it's actually this balance,\nthis web of life, that sustains life."},{"time":67268,"text":"My team and I have been applying\ninsights from ecology to architecture"},{"time":71884,"text":"to see how physical space\ncan help build stronger relationships."},{"time":76304,"text":"The projects I'm going to show you today"},{"time":78290,"text":"use the idea of building relationships\nas the key driver for design."}]},{"cues":[{"time":82852,"text":"Here's an example of what I mean."},{"time":84709,"text":"Recently, we were asked to design\na center for social justice leadership"},{"time":88882,"text":"called the Arcus Center."},{"time":91102,"text":"They asked us for a building\nthat could break down traditional barriers"},{"time":94648,"text":"between different groups"},{"time":95956,"text":"and in doing so, create possibilities\nfor meaningful conversations"},{"time":100227,"text":"around social justice."},{"time":102233,"text":"The students wanted a place\nfor cultural exchange."},{"time":104914,"text":"They thought a place for preparing\nfood together could do that."},{"time":108737,"text":"And they wanted to be welcoming\nto the outside community."},{"time":111492,"text":"They thought a fireplace\ncould draw people in"},{"time":114179,"text":"and help start conversations."},{"time":117553,"text":"And everybody wanted the work\nof social justice to be visible"},{"time":121042,"text":"to the outside world."},{"time":123568,"text":"There really wasn't a precedent\nfor this kind of space,"},{"time":126333,"text":"so we looked around the globe\nand found examples"},{"time":128824,"text":"of community meeting houses."},{"time":130974,"text":"Community meeting houses are places"},{"time":133188,"text":"where there's very specific\nrelationships between people,"},{"time":136573,"text":"like this one in Mali,\nwhere the elders gather."},{"time":140189,"text":"The low roof keeps everybody seated\nand at equal eye level."},{"time":143765,"text":"It's very egalitarian."},{"time":145012,"text":"I mean, you can't stand up\nand take over the meeting."},{"time":147514,"text":"You'd actually bump your head."}]},{"cues":[{"time":149051,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":150728,"text":"In meeting houses,\nthere's always a central space"},{"time":153366,"text":"where you can sit around a circle\nand see each other."},{"time":156041,"text":"So we designed a space just like that"},{"time":158086,"text":"right in the middle of the Arcus Center,"},{"time":160089,"text":"and we anchored it\nwith a fireplace and a kitchen."},{"time":163103,"text":"It's pretty hard to get a kitchen\nand a fireplace in a building like this"},{"time":166599,"text":"with the building codes,"},{"time":167827,"text":"but it was so important\nto the concept, we got it done."},{"time":171288,"text":"And now the central space\nworks for big social gatherings"},{"time":175093,"text":"and a place to meet one-on-one\nfor the very first time."},{"time":178355,"text":"It's almost like\nthis three-way intersection"},{"time":180458,"text":"that encourages bumping into people\nand starting a conversation."},{"time":184676,"text":"Now you can always pass the kitchen\nand see something going on."},{"time":187844,"text":"You can sit by the fireplace\nand share stories."},{"time":191754,"text":"You can study together\nin big groups or in small ones,"},{"time":194975,"text":"because the architecture\nsets up these opportunities."}]},{"cues":[{"time":199641,"text":"Even the construction\nis about building relationships."},{"time":202268,"text":"It's made of cordwood masonry,"},{"time":204153,"text":"which is using logs\nthe way you would use bricks."},{"time":207114,"text":"It's super low-tech and easy to do\nand anyone can do it --"},{"time":210109,"text":"and that's the entire point."},{"time":211810,"text":"The act of making is a social activity."}]},{"cues":[{"time":216412,"text":"And it's good for the planet, too:"},{"time":218444,"text":"the trees absorbed carbon\nwhen they were growing up,"},{"time":221564,"text":"and they gave off oxygen,"},{"time":223232,"text":"and now that carbon\nis trapped inside the walls"},{"time":225997,"text":"and it's not being released\ninto the atmosphere."},{"time":229194,"text":"So making the walls is equivalent\nto taking cars right off the road."},{"time":234149,"text":"We chose the building method"},{"time":236442,"text":"because it connects people\nto each other and to the environment."}]},{"cues":[{"time":241435,"text":"But is it working?"},{"time":242610,"text":"Is it creating relationships\nand nurturing them?"},{"time":244900,"text":"How can we know?"},{"time":246242,"text":"Well, more and more people\nare coming here, for one,"},{"time":249677,"text":"and as a result of the fireside chats"},{"time":252021,"text":"and a full calendar of programming,"},{"time":254143,"text":"people are applying\nfor the Arcus Fellowships."},{"time":256755,"text":"In fact, applications have increased\ntenfold for the Arcus Fellowship"},{"time":261078,"text":"since the building opened."},{"time":262367,"text":"It's working. It's bringing\npeople together."}]},{"cues":[{"time":266254,"text":"So I've shown how architecture\ncan connect people"},{"time":268646,"text":"on this kind of horizontal campus scale."},{"time":271345,"text":"But we wondered if social relationships\ncould be scaled up --"},{"time":274867,"text":"or rather, upward -- in tall buildings."},{"time":278381,"text":"Tall buildings don't necessarily lend\nthemselves to being social buildings."},{"time":282442,"text":"They can seem isolating and inward."},{"time":284826,"text":"You might only see people\nin those awkward elevator rides."},{"time":290676,"text":"But in several major cities,\nI've been designing tall buildings"},{"time":294211,"text":"that are based on creating\nrelationships between people."}]},{"cues":[{"time":297576,"text":"This is Aqua."},{"time":299076,"text":"It's a residential high-rise in Chicago"},{"time":302674,"text":"aimed at young urban professionals\nand empty nesters,"},{"time":305309,"text":"many of them new to the city."},{"time":307817,"text":"With over 700 apartments, we wanted to see\nif we could use architecture"},{"time":311767,"text":"to help people get to know\ntheir neighbors,"},{"time":313862,"text":"even when their homes are organized\nin the vertical dimension."},{"time":319088,"text":"So we invented a way to use balconies\nas the new social connectors."},{"time":323569,"text":"The shapes of the floor slabs\nvary slightly and they transition"},{"time":327133,"text":"as you go up the tower."},{"time":328526,"text":"The result of this\nis that you can actually see people"},{"time":332451,"text":"from your balcony."},{"time":333820,"text":"The balconies are misregistered."},{"time":335977,"text":"You can lean over your balcony\nand say, \"Hey!\""},{"time":338145,"text":"just like you would across the backyard."},{"time":341147,"text":"To make the balconies more comfortable"},{"time":343050,"text":"for a longer period of time\nduring the year,"},{"time":345351,"text":"we studied the wind\nwith digital simulations,"},{"time":347841,"text":"so the effect of the balcony shapes\nbreaks up the wind"},{"time":350727,"text":"and confuses the wind"},{"time":352062,"text":"and makes the balconies\nmore comfortable and less windy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":356110,"text":"Now, just by being able\nto go outside on your balcony"},{"time":359083,"text":"or on the third floor roof terrace,"},{"time":361182,"text":"you can be connected to the outdoors,"},{"time":363291,"text":"even when you're way above\nthe ground plane."},{"time":365446,"text":"So the building acts to create community"},{"time":368205,"text":"within the building and the city\nat the same time."},{"time":370850,"text":"It's working."},{"time":372863,"text":"And people are starting to meet each other\non the building surface"},{"time":376887,"text":"and we've heard --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":378067,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":379147,"text":"they've even starting getting\ntogether as couples."},{"time":382756,"text":"But besides romantic relationships,"},{"time":385407,"text":"the building has a positive social effect"},{"time":387671,"text":"on the community,"},{"time":389632,"text":"as evidenced by people\nstarting groups together"},{"time":392343,"text":"and starting big projects together,"},{"time":394213,"text":"like this organic community garden\non the building's roof terrace."}]},{"cues":[{"time":399874,"text":"So I've shown how tall buildings\ncan be social connectors,"},{"time":402914,"text":"but what about public architecture?"},{"time":404930,"text":"How can we create better\nsocial cohesion in public buildings"},{"time":408817,"text":"and civic spaces,"},{"time":410198,"text":"and why is it important?"},{"time":412070,"text":"Public architecture\nis just not as successful"},{"time":414191,"text":"if it comes from the top down."}]},{"cues":[{"time":417493,"text":"About 15 years ago in Chicago,"},{"time":419615,"text":"they started to replace\nold police stations,"},{"time":422746,"text":"and they built this identical model\nall over the city."},{"time":426499,"text":"And even though they had good intentions"},{"time":429084,"text":"of treating all neighborhoods equally,"},{"time":431606,"text":"the communities didn't feel\ninvested in the process"},{"time":434050,"text":"or feel a sense of ownership\nof these buildings."},{"time":436588,"text":"It was equality in the sense that\neverybody gets the same police station,"},{"time":440139,"text":"but it wasn't equity\nin the sense of responding"},{"time":443517,"text":"to each community's individual needs."},{"time":445899,"text":"And equity is the key issue here."}]},{"cues":[{"time":448764,"text":"You know, in my field, there's a debate"},{"time":452188,"text":"about whether architecture\ncan even do anything"},{"time":454803,"text":"to improve social relationships."},{"time":457012,"text":"But I believe that we need architecture\nand every tool in our tool kit"},{"time":462470,"text":"to improve these relationships."},{"time":465313,"text":"In the US, policy reforms\nhave been recommended"},{"time":468720,"text":"in order to rebuild trust."},{"time":470548,"text":"But my team and I wondered"},{"time":471980,"text":"if design and a more inclusive\ndesign process"},{"time":475043,"text":"could help add something positive\nto this policy conversation."},{"time":478720,"text":"We asked ourselves simply:"},{"time":480430,"text":"Can design help rebuild trust?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":483108,"text":"So we reached out to community members\nand police officers in North Lawndale;"},{"time":487454,"text":"it's a neighborhood in Chicago"},{"time":489037,"text":"where the police station\nis perceived as a scary fortress"},{"time":491877,"text":"surrounded by a parking lot."},{"time":494254,"text":"In North Lawndale,\npeople are afraid of police"},{"time":496896,"text":"and of going anywhere\nnear the police station,"},{"time":499125,"text":"even to report a crime."},{"time":500843,"text":"So we organized this brainstorming session"},{"time":503620,"text":"with both groups participating,"},{"time":505302,"text":"and we came up with this whole\nnew idea for the police station."},{"time":509141,"text":"It's called \"Polis Station.\""},{"time":511070,"text":"\"Polis\" is a Greek word that means\na place with a sense of community."},{"time":516528,"text":"It's based on the idea"},{"time":518172,"text":"that if you can increase opportunities\nfor positive social interactions"},{"time":522133,"text":"between police and community members,"},{"time":524450,"text":"you can rebuild that relationship"},{"time":526669,"text":"and activate the neighborhood\nat the same time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":530183,"text":"Instead of the police station\nas a scary fortress,"},{"time":533312,"text":"you get highly active spaces\non the public side of the station --"},{"time":537793,"text":"places that spark conversation,"},{"time":539327,"text":"like a barbershop, a coffee shop"},{"time":541911,"text":"or sports courts as well."},{"time":543508,"text":"Both cops and kids said they love sports."},{"time":546339,"text":"These insights came directly\nfrom the community members"},{"time":549754,"text":"and the police officers themselves,"},{"time":552110,"text":"and as designers, our role\nwas just to connect the dots"},{"time":555893,"text":"and suggest the first step."},{"time":557853,"text":"So with the help\nof the city and the parks,"},{"time":560491,"text":"we were able to raise funds\nand design and build a half-court,"},{"time":564801,"text":"right on the police station parking lot."}]},{"cues":[{"time":567165,"text":"It's a start."},{"time":568630,"text":"But is it rebuilding trust?"},{"time":570854,"text":"The people in North Lawndale say\nthe kids are using the courts every day"},{"time":574454,"text":"and they even organize tournaments\nlike this one shown here,"},{"time":577827,"text":"and once in a while an officer joins in."},{"time":582264,"text":"But now, they even have basketballs\ninside the station"},{"time":584954,"text":"that kids can borrow."},{"time":586243,"text":"And recently they've asked us\nto expand the courts"},{"time":588759,"text":"and build a park on the site."},{"time":592639,"text":"And parents report something astonishing."},{"time":595491,"text":"Before, there was fear of going\nanywhere the station, and now they say"},{"time":599746,"text":"there's a sense that the court is safer\nthan other courts nearby,"},{"time":603257,"text":"and they prefer their kids to play here."}]},{"cues":[{"time":606277,"text":"So maybe in the future,"},{"time":607891,"text":"on the public side of the station,"},{"time":609561,"text":"you might be able to drop in\nfor a haircut at the barbershop"},{"time":613290,"text":"or reserve the community room\nfor a birthday party"},{"time":615963,"text":"or renew your driver's license"},{"time":617630,"text":"or get money out of an ATM."},{"time":620204,"text":"It can be a place for neighbors\nto meet each other"},{"time":622919,"text":"and to get to know\nthe officers, and vice versa."},{"time":626781,"text":"This is not a utopian fantasy."},{"time":628749,"text":"It's about how do you design\nto rebuild trust,"},{"time":632761,"text":"trusting relationships?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":635009,"text":"You know, every city has parks,\nlibraries, schools"},{"time":638824,"text":"and other public buildings"},{"time":640242,"text":"that have the potential\nto be reimagined as social connectors."},{"time":645134,"text":"But reimagining the buildings\nfor the future is going to require"},{"time":649188,"text":"engaging the people who live there."},{"time":651979,"text":"Engaging the public can be intimidating,\nand I've felt that, too."},{"time":655891,"text":"But maybe that's because\nin architecture school,"},{"time":658196,"text":"we don't really learn how to engage\nthe public in the act of design."},{"time":662227,"text":"We're taught to defend\nour design against criticism."},{"time":665774,"text":"But I think that can change, too."}]},{"cues":[{"time":668993,"text":"So if we can focus the design mind"},{"time":671590,"text":"on creating positive,\nreinforcing relationships"},{"time":675594,"text":"in architecture and through architecture,"},{"time":677598,"text":"I believe we can do much more\nthan create individual buildings."},{"time":682245,"text":"We can reduce the stress\nand the polarization"},{"time":685464,"text":"in our urban habitats."},{"time":688280,"text":"We can create relationships."},{"time":690169,"text":"We can help steady\nthis planet we all share."}]},{"cues":[{"time":694142,"text":"See?"},{"time":695325,"text":"Architects really are\nrelationship builders."}]},{"cues":[{"time":697588,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":698974,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":700150,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}